عُلبَة(عُلَب):box/tin/packet: 14* : Also "chest, trunk; can". From the root ع ل ب (ʿ-l-b).

لُعبَة(لُعَب):toy/game: 14

تُحْفة(تُحَف):masterpiece/artefact: 14 : Also "work of art, gift, rarity" (not in WK). Compare مَتْحَف "museum"

دَوْلَة(دُوَل):nation/state: 14 : Also "alteration, change". From the root د و ل‎ (d-w-l) "related to alternating, to the state."

رَجُل/رِجَال:man: 14* : From the root ر ج ل‎ (r-j-l). Compare رَجِلَ "to go on foot, to walk"

جَبَل/جِبَال:mountain: 14*

جَمَل(جِمَال):camel: 14

بَحْر(بِحَار):sea/seas: 14* : Also "large river; a noble or great man". From Proto-Semitic *baḥr- (“sea”), from the root ب ح ر‎ (b-ḥ-r) "related to spaciousness"

ريح(رِياح):wind: 14 : Also "fart; smell, odor". From the root ر ي ح‎ (r-y-ḥ). From Proto-Semitic *rūḥ- (“to blow, breathe; spirit”). Cognate with Hebrew רוּחַ‎ (rúach), Aramaic ܪܘܼܚܵܐ‎/רוּחָא‎ (rūħā)

حَال(أحوال):state/condition: 14 : From the root ح و ل‎ (ḥ-w-l) "forms words relating to change"

الطَّقْس:the weather: 14* : Also "ritual; liturgy; clerical rank". From Classical Syriac ܛܟܣܐ‎ (ṭekkəsā), from Ancient Greek τάξις (táxis, “arrangement”). Apparently a late 19th century borrowing (WK)

دَرَجَة اَلْحَرَارَة:temperature ("degree of heat"): 14 : Remember the "t" - "darajat al-ḥarāra"

حَارّ:hot: 14* : Derived from the active participle of حَرَّ‎ (ḥarra, “to be hot”), from the root ح ر ر‎ (ḥ-r-r).

مُعْتَدِل:mild/moderate: 14 : Not in WK, but see عَدَلَ "to act justly; to make (someone) equal"

شَمْس:sun: 14 : From the root ش م س‎ (š-m-s), the noun “sun” inherited from Proto-Semitic *śamš-.

مُشْمِس:sunny: 14

غَيْم(غُيوم):cloud: 14 : Collective noun (singulative غَيْمَة‎ (ḡayma))

غائِم:cloudy/overcast: 14

مَطَر(أَمْطار):rain: 14

مُمْطِر:rainy: 14

شَديد:strong/heavy: 14

فَتْرَة(فَتَرَات):period (of time): 14

سَماء صافِية:clear sky: 14 :صَافِيَة • (ṣāfiya) f = feminine singular of صَافٍ‎ (ṣāfin), derived from the active participle of صَفَا‎ (ṣafā, “to be clear, to be serene, to devote oneself wholeheartedly”), from the root ص ف و‎ (ṣ-f-w).

سَمَاء : sky : 14+ : سَمَاء • (samāʾ) f (dual سَمَاوَانِ‎ (samāwāni) or سَمَاءَانِ‎ (samāʾāni), plural سَمَاوَات‎ (samāwāt) or سَمٰوَات‎ (samāwāt)) sky, heaven; firmament. From the root س م و‎ (s-m-w). From Proto-Semitic *šamāy- (“sky, heaven”). Cognate with Akkadian šamû.

رِحْلة(رِحْلات):trip/journey: 14 : From the root ر ح ل‎ (r-ḥ-l) "related to departure and saddlebags"; compare رَحَلَ‎ (raḥala, “to depart”).

مُمْتِع:enjoyable: 14 : Compare مُتْعَة "enjoyment, delight, pleasure"

لَذيذ:tasty/delicious: 14 : Etymology unknown

يَوم(أَيّام):day: 14* : From the root ي و م‎ (y-w-m). From Proto-Semitic *yawm-. Compare "Yom Kippur"

آخِر يَوْم:the last day: 14

دَيْر(أَدْيِرة):monastery: 14 : Borrowed from Classical Syriac ܕܝܪܐ‎ (dayrā) which generally means “dwelling” and specifically “cloister”, from the Syriac root ܕ-ܘ-ܪ‎ (d-w-r) relating to dwelling. Not from the Arabic root د و ر‎ (d-w-r) as this means “spinning” and does not fit semantically (WK)

صَديق(أَصْدِقاء):friend: 14 : From the root ص د ق‎ (ṣ-d-q) "forms words related to truth; forms words related to friends, friendship, acquaintance or companionship"; from Proto-Semitic, cognate with Hebrew צ־ד־ק‎.

فُنْدُق(فَنادِق):hotel: 14* : From Ancient Greek πανδοκεῖον (pandokeîon), "inn". From πᾰν- (pan-, “all, every”) + δοκ- (dok-), o-grade of the stem of δέχομαι (dékhomai, “to receive”), + -εῖον (-eîon).

مَسْبَح(مَسابِح):swimming pool: 14 : Noun of place from the verb سَبَحَ‎ (sabaḥa, “to swim”), from the root س ب ح‎ (s-b-ḥ). Compare سَبَّحَ‎ (sabbaḥa, “to glorify, to praise”) (word used in Muslim prayer)

شُروق الشَّمْس:sunrise: 14

الأُسْبوع الماضي:last week: 14 : الْمَاضِي • (al-māḍī) m = Nominalized definite state of مَاضٍ‎ (māḍin, “past”). Derived from the active participle of مَضَى‎ (maḍā, “to pass”), from the root م ض ي‎ (m-ḍ-y).

أُسْبُوع :week:14-:In memrize but not in textbook. From س ب ع‎ (s-b-ʿ); compare سَبْعَة‎ (sabʿa), seven. Compare with Hebrew שבוע‎ (šavúaʿ, “week”) and Hebrew שבע‎ (šévaʿ, “seven”)

